&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every year, millions of families start the school search process. Students wade through a sea of information and decisions to make, and unfortunately access to help hasn’t changed much in decades: it’s not super clear what your options are, and you might not feel confident that a school is right for them, or think you’ll be able to afford it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Niche is on a mission to make researching and enrolling in schools easy, transparent, and free. Students need support choosing a school and paying for their education, schools want to find students who will thrive on their campus, and families need help supporting their students every step of the way. Niche helps ensure that it’s not just students already confident about college who get enrolled and can afford to attend.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Senior Product Designer to continuously improve our partner school experiences focused on AI-generated message content and student-level personalized communication across web and mobile. Several of these features are brand new and we need your expertise to refine and enhance them in order to get more students connected with schools who are interested in them specifically, helping the school’s authentic voice shine through and ensuring touch points help nurture students productively toward becoming fully enrolled. You will play a critical role in a growing space, working closely with cross-functional teams on creating seamless, effective experiences that determine the future of personalized school application and enrollment.&lt;/p&gt;
